data.chText: 诊断（疾病）；判断（问题的原因）
data.enText: to say exactly what an illness or the cause of a problem is

data.chText: 此项化验可用于诊断多种疾病。
data.enText: The test is used to diagnose a variety of diseases.
The illness was diagnosed as cancer.

data.chText: 他最近被诊断出患有心绞痛。
data.enText: He has recently been diagnosed with angina.

data.chText: 他64岁时被诊断患有糖尿病。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: He was diagnosed (as) a diabetic when he was 64.

tr: determine or distinguish the nature of a problem or an illness through a diagnostic analysis

value.def: If someone or something is diagnosed as having a particular illness or problem, their illness or problem is identified. If an illness or problem is diagnosed, it is identified.

example.ex: The soldiers were diagnosed as having flu...
example.tran: 这些士兵经诊断患了流感。

example.ex: Susan had a mental breakdown and was diagnosed with schizophrenia...
example.tran: 苏珊精神崩溃，被诊断为得了精神分裂症。

example.ex: In 1894 her illness was diagnosed as cancer...
He could diagnose an engine problem simply by listening...
example.tran: 他仅靠听就能判断发动机出了什么问题。

example.ex: This disorder is easily diagnosed but not so easily treated.
example.tran: 这种疾病容易诊断，但却不容易治疗。
